<HEADLINE>
<P>
50 FEARED DEAD, 1,000 HURT IN FIERCE BANGLADESH STORM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DHAKA, Bangladesh 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A severe storm in northern Bangladesh may have killed up to 50 people and 
injured more than 1,000, officials said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Rescuers have found 30 bodies, and at least 20 people were still missing 40 
hours after Friday night's storm, which packed winds of 85 m.p.h., authorities 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
