ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; 
</P>
<P>
TRUCK-THEFT SUSPECT RAMS CAR IN CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM CARLTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorist being pursued by police on Saturday night crashed a stolen pickup 
truck after ramming a patrol car and driving through a fence, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The motorist, James Scott Blazevich, 27, identified by police as a transient 
formerly of Garden Grove, was held in Cypress City Jail on suspicion of felony 
assault of a police officer, possession of stolen property and reckless 
evading. 
</P>
<P>
His bail was set at $50,000. 
</P>
<P>
The chase started about 9:25 p.m. Saturday when Patrolman Tom Bruce spotted the 
suspect driving erratically in a 1980 Toyota pickup truck near the intersection 
of Knott and Cerritos avenues, Cypress Police Sgt. John Avila said. The suspect 
speeded up as Bruce tried to pull him over. 
</P>
<P>
During a brief but wild chase, Avila said, the suspect rammed an Orange County 
sheriff's vehicle assisting in the pursuit and drove through a railroad 
retaining fence. The chase ended when the suspect crashed the truck into a tree 
on Katella Avenue east of Beach Boulevard, Avila said. JIM CARLTON 
</P>
