<HEADLINE>
<P>
CUBS' SANDBERG SETS ERROR-FREE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ryne Sandberg set a major league record for second basemen with his 480th 
consecutive errorless play Sunday for the Chicago Cubs. 
</P>
<P>
Sandberg caught a throw from third baseman Luis Salazar in the fifth inning, 
forcing Pittsburgh's Wally Backman at second. 
</P>
<P>
Sandberg broke the previous mark of 479 chances set by Philadelphia's Manny 
Trillo from April 8 to July 31, 1982. Trillo's stretch extended over 89 games, 
plus two partial games. The game, won by Pittsburgh, 3-2, was Sandberg's 102nd 
in a row without an error. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
