<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gebre Tedese led a 1-2-3-4 Ethiopian finish in the Rome Marathon on a course 
that turned out to be shorter than the regulation 26 miles, 385 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Tedese was timed in 2:10:28. However, after the race, officials determined that 
the course was about 25 yards short. 
</P>
<P>
The women's winner was Silvana Cucchietti of Italy, in 2:34:21. 
</P>
