<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States won its first game and Sweden handed the Soviet Union its 
first loss in five years at the World Hockey Championships in Bern, 
Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
The Americans took a 5-0 lead and held off a rally to beat West Germany, 6-3, 
for their first victory after four consecutive losses. 
</P>
<P>
The Swedes got a tiebreaking goal from Hakan Loob and beat the Soviets, 3-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
