<P>
SANTA ANA BOY, 8, SHOT BY DRIVE-BY ASSAILANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVAN MAHARAJ and JIM CARLTON, TIMES STAFF WRITERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the third straight night gunfire from suspected gang members ripped through 
a Santa Ana neighborhood Sunday, striking a young boy in the back as he watched 
television and a woman who was sleeping in the next room, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Carlos Alvarez, 8, of Santa Ana was in serious condition at UCI Medical Center 
today with a single gunshot wound. The same bullet, police said, also grazed 
30-year-old Oselia Rojas, who was treated at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting was the latest in a wave of gang-related violence in Santa Ana 
that has left two teen-agers dead and three people wounded since Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Sunday's incident occurred around 10:45 p.m. as Carlos was watching television 
in his living room in the 2700 block of West Lingan Lane. 
</P>
<P>
Antonio Torres, a family friend who lives at the house, said a bullet burst 
through the wall, penetrated the boy's chair, tore through his upper back and 
exited his stomach. 
</P>
<P>
The same bullet, Torres said, then ripped through another wall before striking 
Rojas. 
</P>
<P>
"If my head had been moved over another inch, I would have been dead," Rojas 
said today during an interview at the Lingan Lane house. 
</P>
<P>
It was the fifth drive-by shooting at the house in three years, Torres said. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana police spokeswoman Maureen Thomas said investigators have not 
determined a motive for the attack, but Torres said it could have been aimed at 
another nephew who previously lived at the house and is a reputed gang member. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas said police are trying to determine if the shooting is connected to two 
others that claimed the lives of two teen-agers over the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
On Friday night, 17-year-old Roger Ochoa died after being shot four times in 
the back during a fight at a birthday party with suspected gang members. And 
15-year-old Cesar Salgado was gunned down early Sunday as he and a friend were 
walking away from another party, about nine blocks away from Friday's shooting. 
He died at UCI Medical Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
