<P>
MARLA LIFTS PRIMETIME RATINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The appearance of Marla Maples -- the former girlfriend of Donald Trump -- on 
"PrimeTime Live" Thursday night turned out to be something of a ratings 
success. 
</P>
<P>
The interview, by ABC'S Diane Sawyer, wound up with a 14.2 national Nielsen 
rating and a 25% audience share. 
</P>
<P>
That's the highest ever for the program -- the previous best was a 12.6 
rating-22% share on Oct. 19 following the San Francisco earthquake -- and it 
enabled "PrimeTime Live" to win the 10-to-11 time period for the first time. 
</P>
<P>
Maples' appearance in the last half hour of the program jumped "PrimeTime's" 
ratings in New York, where she has been in tabloid heaven for weeks, to a 
23.4-37 from a 21.3-31 in the first 30 minutes. 
