<P>
ANTHONY QUINN'S ART DISPLAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MEXICO CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An exhibit of actor Anthony Quinn's paintings and sculptures is to open Tuesday 
at the National History Museum in Chapultepec Castle. 
</P>
<P>
Quinn, born in the state of Chihuahua, will donate to the museum two sculptures 
and a collection of American Indian writings illustrated with 20 of his 
lithographs, the government news agency Notimex said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The exhibit will include 40 sculptures and six paintings. 
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Quinn, 75, as saying that he is glad to be recognized as a 
Mexican and that having his work exhibited in Mexico is the fulfillment of a 
dream. 
